GENRES = ['Action', 'Adventure', 'Animation', 'Children', 'Comedy', 'Crime',
            'Documentary', 'Drama', 'Fantasy', 'FilmNoir', 'Horror', 'Musical',
            'Mystery', 'Romance', 'SciFi', 'Thriller', 'War', 'Western']
In [3]:
response = requests.get('http://localhost:5000/top-5-rated-movies-each-genres')
decoded_response = response.json()

columns = ['movie', 'year', 'numRatings', 'avgRating', 'scale']


dict_repr = dict()
for rowno, obj in enumerate(decoded_response):
    for i in range(5): 
        dict_repr[rowno * 5 + i] = [obj['genre']] + [obj['data'][i][c] for c in columns]

df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(dict_repr, orient='index', columns=['genre'] + columns)
df.set_index('genre', inplace=True)

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15, 30))
fig.suptitle('Top 5 most rated movie of each genre', fontsize='x-large')
fig.subplots_adjust(top=0.955)
group_bar_width = 2
Ngenres = len(GENRES)

for i in range(3):
    ax = plt.subplot(3, 1, i + 1)
    ax.set_xlim(right=120000)

    sub_genres = GENRES[6 * i: 6 * i + 6]
    for j, genre in enumerate(sub_genres):
        curr_genre_df = df[:][df.index == genre].sort_values(by='numRatings', ascending=False)
        rects = []
        for k in range(5):
            offset = (k - 2) * 0.12
            rects.extend(
                plt.barh(y=j + offset, width=curr_genre_df.iloc[k]['numRatings'], height=group_bar_width / Ngenres)
            )
        for k, rect in enumerate(rects):
            if not np.isnan(rect.get_height()):
                ax.text(x=rect.get_width() + 15, y=rect.get_y() + 0.04, 
                        s=curr_genre_df.iloc[k]['movie'] + ' (' + str(curr_genre_df.iloc[k]['numRatings']) + ')', 
                        fontsize=9)

    ax.set_ylabel('Genres')
    ax.set_xlabel('Number of ratings')
    
    ax.set_yticklabels([''] + sub_genres)

    
plt.show()

response = requests.get('http://localhost:5000/tags-wordcloud-v2')
decoded_response = response.json()

wordcloud = WordCloud(width=1200, height=800).generate_from_frequencies(
    {ele['tag']: ele['count'] for ele in decoded_response} 
)
plt.figure(figsize =(20, 30))
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation="bilinear")
plt.axis("off")
plt.show()
